{
  "texts": [
    "Table 7 summarizes the applications of the graph pooling methods.",
    "The application of graph neural networks and their pooling strategies has demonstrated significant advantages and innovations in the field of bioinformatics, especially in complex tasks such as protein-protein interaction prediction, synergistic drug combination prediction, protein function prediction, and tissue cellular neighborhoods (TCNs) identification.",
    "In protein interaction prediction, (Gligorijević et al. 2021) (Jha et al. 2022) simplified the subsequent analysis process by introducing a global pooling technique to ensure that all proteins are uniformly characterized as fixed-size vectors.",
    "Meanwhile, (Gao et al. 2023) further explored hierarchical pooling methods, especially SAGPool and average aggregation operations, which are strategies that not only maintain the stability of the model output but also enhance the ability of the model to capture subtle differences among proteins.",
    "In synergistic drug combination prediction, (Dong et al. 2023) proposed the node and edge pooling method based on the self-attention mechanism (SANEpool), which skillfully combines gene features and topology information to assign importance scores to genes and connections, effectively copes with the problem of high centrality of gene nodes in molecular networks."
  ]
}